    <section>
        <h1>Our Programs</h1>
        <p><strong>Child Care Institutions (CCI):</strong> JSVK operates CCIs in Jamtara and Saraikela Kharsawan districts under the Mission Vatsalya program. These institutions provide a safe and nurturing environment for vulnerable children, offering education, health services, counseling, and vocational training. The program also focuses on reintegrating children into society. <strong>Impact:</strong> Over 100 children have successfully transitioned into mainstream society, showcasing improved educational and psychological outcomes.</p>

        <p><strong>Jute Resource cum Production Centre:</strong> This initiative empowers rural artisans by providing them with the skills needed to produce eco-friendly jute products. Participants undergo training in designing, stitching, and quality control. The program promotes sustainable alternatives to plastic and creates market-ready products. <strong>Impact:</strong> Over 120 artisans have been trained, leading to increased income and reduced plastic usage.</p>

        <p><strong>Awareness Workshop on Tribal Empowerment:</strong> Focused on empowering tribal women, these workshops provide hands-on training in jute handicrafts. Participants learn essential skills to create marketable products, enabling them to earn a sustainable livelihood. <strong>Impact:</strong> Over 30 tribal women have enhanced their economic self-reliance and reduced dependence on seasonal work.</p>

        <p><strong>Pradhan Mantri Aadi Adarsh Gram Yojna (PMAAGY):</strong> Under this scheme, JSVK has developed comprehensive village plans for 52 tribal villages. Key activities include water harvesting, sanitation improvement, and livelihood development. <strong>Impact:</strong> Over 15,000 individuals now have better access to water and improved hygiene facilities.</p>

        <p><strong>Health and Sanitation:</strong> JSVK's health programs focus on hygiene education and infrastructure development, such as soak pits near hand pumps. These efforts address waterborne diseases and promote community-led sanitation initiatives. <strong>Impact:</strong> Health outcomes for over 5,000 households have significantly improved.</p>

        <p><strong>Humanitarian Initiatives:</strong> During harsh winters, JSVK distributes blankets and organizes health camps for the homeless. These efforts provide immediate relief and improved living conditions for vulnerable populations. <strong>Impact:</strong> Over 10,000 individuals have benefitted from these humanitarian programs.</p>

        <p><strong>Har Ghar Tiranga Abhiyan:</strong> This campaign fosters a sense of patriotism and community spirit by encouraging households to hoist the national flag. <strong>Impact:</strong> Over 1,000 households participated, promoting unity and pride.</p>

        <p><strong>Save Environment:</strong> JSVK actively promotes afforestation and eco-friendly alternatives to plastics. Programs include tree plantation drives and the distribution of biodegradable products. <strong>Impact:</strong> 20,000 trees have been planted, and plastic usage has decreased in five districts.</p>
